# PMCA Tools — feature development

## Branches

- **`main`** — stable; treat `PMCA Tools.html` as frozen unless the user explicitly wants integration work.
- **`development`** — default branch for new work (feature folders, server tweaks, docs).

## Where to add code

- **New UI/features:** `features/<feature-name>/` using the same pattern as `networth/` and `partnership/` (`index.html`, `app.js`, `styles.css`).
- **Avoid** editing `PMCA Tools.html` for early work; the user can open new pages directly via `http://localhost:3000/features/<feature-name>/index.html` after `npm start`.

## When to touch the monolith

Only when the user asks to **embed** a feature in the main dashboard (nav links, shared styles). Prefer small, reviewable edits.

## Data and API

- Respect `.gitignore` for `Data/`, `node_modules/`, `.env`.
- New HTTP endpoints in `server.js` only when needed; keep changes minimal and documented in commit messages.
